{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2f4b73b-a7fc-452f-b96a-b71ed8329c48","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory. I do have `dotnet` available and can install `dotnet-dump` for analysis.\n\n**Could you tell me:**\n1. **Where is your `.dmp` file located?** (full path or upload it)\n2. **Which .NET version** is your app targeting? (e.g., .NET 6, 8, 9)\n\nIn the meantime, here's the general approach I'll use once we have the dump:\n\n```\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\nKey commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show the last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\nLet me know the file location and I'll walk through the analysis with you!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f00bc4e-0ba7-4139-9b95-47f4569f5c3f","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"6002:281228:E20FCB:1061A88:69EACBFC"},"id":"44c3b8bb-39b0-487e-880d-40dc20e2d830","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:49:03.136Z","parentId":"115d2565-764b-4eaf-8b9d-6c8cb5376fe8"}
